      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/nahj-al-balagha:3:477:1",
      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/32/3/470/597",
      "text": [
        " (عليه السلام): التَّوْحِيدُ أَلَّا تَتَوَهَّمَهُ وَالْعَدْلُ أَلَّا تَتَّهِمَهُ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.sayed-ali-raza": [
          "470. Amīr al-mu’minīn, peace be upon him, was asked on the Unity of Allāh and His justice, when he replied: Unity means that you do not subject Him to the limitations of your imagination and justice means that you do not lay any blame on Him. [1]"
        ]
      }
